  "body": "versions:\r\nsolidity 0.5.16;\r\nhardhat 2.10.2\r\n\r\nI have this sol code:\r\n```\r\nuint32 blockNumber = safe32(getBlockNumber(), \"block number exceeds 32 bits\");\r\nconsole.log(\"blockNumber: \", blockNumber);\r\nconsole.log(\"getBlockNumber(): \", getBlockNumber());\r\nconsole.log(\"block.number: \", block.number);\r\n\r\nfunction getBlockNumber() public view returns (uint) {\r\n        return block.number;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen I run test, I get these logs:\r\n`blockNumber:  0\r\n  getBlockNumber():  0\r\n  block.number:  23\r\n`\r\n\r\nAs you can see, `block.number` is working in hardhat test. But after it is wrapped in `getBlockNumber() `, it become 0. ",
